text: Mother Nature‚Äô irony: The worst #redtide in recent memory on #AnnaMariaIsland #Florida has been accompanied by the best year in recorded history for #seaturtle nesting. So far, AMI Turtle Watch has recorded 521 nests as of Sunday, breaking the record set in 2017 (488 nests) . https   twitter com MRMasferrer status 1031292555856674816 photo 1
name: Marc R. Masferrer
text_with_display_links: Mother Nature‚Äô irony: The worst #redtide in recent memory on #AnnaMariaIsland #Florida has been accompanied by the best year in recorded history for #seaturtle nesting. So far, AMI Turtle Watch has recorded 521 nests as of Sunday, breaking the record set in 2017 (488 nests) https://t.co/uGWpMypRcJ

text: Of those nests, 243 have hatched an estimated 19,400 baby sea turtles. Of those an estimated 19 or 20 - if they are female - will reach sexual maturity in 25-35 years & return to AMI or nearby to nest
name: Marc R. Masferrer
text_with_display_links: NA

text: With those odds, it‚Äôs easy to see the importance of protecting every baby turtle possible
name: Marc R. Masferrer
text_with_display_links: NA

text: Fortunately, #redtide is not as big a threat to baby turtles as much as birds, ghost crabs, fish & lights left on by visitors to the beach. Keep it dark because when they disorient they get tired making it harder to swim past the red tide
name: Marc R. Masferrer
text_with_display_links: NA
